Design is not about making things &quot;look pretty&quot; &#8212; it&#8217;s about improving our lives. Who doesn&#8217;t want to sit in a comfier chair or drive a more ergonomic car?For an intriguing glimpse into the minds of the people who have made good design their raison d&#8217;&#234;tre, watch Abstract: The Art of Design on Netflix.Each of the episodes in this eight-part series is dedicated to a designer at the top of his or her field. There&#8217;s acclaimed illustrator Paula Scher, and Bjarke Ingels, the architect whose crazy, futurist structures include the 2 World Trade Centre building that&#8217;s in the pipeline for New York City. Other subjects include Ilse Crawford, the godmother of interior design, and footwear designer Tinker Hatfield.